==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bonus
<hw>Bo"nus</hw> <pr>(b⟦omac⟧"n⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Bonuses</plw> <pr>(-⟦ecr⟧z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>bonus</ets> good. Cf. <er>Bonny</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A premium given for a loan, or for a charter or
other privilege granted to a company; <as>as the bank paid a
<ex>bonus</ex> for its charter</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An extra dividend to the shareholders of a joint
stock company, out of accumulated profits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Money paid in addition to a stated
compensation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bon vivant</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
